{{Infobox football biography | name = Farid Daoud | image = Farid Daoud.jpg | caption = | fullname = Farid Daoud | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1989|8|25|mf=yes}} | birth_place = [[Tizi Ouzou]], [[Algeria]] | height = | position = [[Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[USM Annaba]] | clubnumber = 23 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[JS Kabylie]] | youthyears2 = | youthclubs2 = [[MC Alger]] | years1 = 2007–2014 | clubs1 = [[MC Alger]] | caps1 = 80 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2014–2015 | clubs2 = [[RC Arbaâ]] | caps2 = 45 | goals2 = 1 | years3 = 2016 | clubs3 = [[DRB Tadjenanet]] | caps3 = 13 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2016–2017 | clubs4 = [[CA Batna]] | caps4 = 22 | goals4 = 0 | years5 = 2017–2018 | clubs5 = [[USM El Harrach]] | caps5 = ? | goals5 = 0 | years6 = 2018– | clubs6 = [[USM Annaba]] | caps6 = ? | goals6 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2008 | nationalyears2 = 2009– | nationalteam1 = [[Algeria national under-20 football team|Algeria U20]] | nationalteam2 = [[Algeria Olympic football team|Algeria U23]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalcaps2 = 8 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | medaltemplates = | club-update = 00:00, 30 March 2011 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 00:00, 30 November 2011 (UTC) }} '''Farid Daoud''' (born August 25, 1989 in [[Tizi Ouzou]]) is an [[Algeria]]n [[Association football|football]] player. He currently plays for [[USM Annaba]] in the [[Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 2]].
==Club career== Daoud began his career in the junior ranks of his hometown club of [[JS Kabylie]].<ref>[http://www.lebuteur.com/ligue-1/actualites/mca-cest-au-tour-de-daoud-de-sortir-de-lanonymat MCA : C'est au tour de Daoud de sortir de l'anonymat] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403215006/http://www.lebuteur.com/ligue-1/actualites/mca-cest-au-tour-de-daoud-de-sortir-de-lanonymat |date=2012-04-03 }}</ref> He left the club briefly to pursue his studies at the USTO before returning to continue his playing career. In 2007, he left JSK to join [[MC Alger]].
On December 12, 2007, Daoud made his professional debut for [[MC Alger]] in a league game against [[WA Tlemcen]]. Daoud came on as a substitute in the 70th minute with the game ending 0–0.<ref>[http://www.dzfoot.com/fiche-3536.php MCA 0–0 WAT] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120921145110/http://www.dzfoot.com/fiche-3536.php |date=2012-09-21 }}</ref>
==International career== On September 14, 2009, Daoud was called up by coach [[Abdelhak Benchikha]] to the [[Algeria Olympic football team|Algerian Under-23 National Team]] for a ten-day training camp in [[France]].<ref>[http://www.dzfoot.com/news-4832/en-espoirs-l-en-en-regroupement-a-beaucaire/ EN Espoirs : L'EN en regroupement à Beaucaire]</ref> In December 2010, he was a member of the Under-23 team that won the [[2010 UNAF U-23 Tournament]] in [[Morocco]]. On November 16, 2011, he was selected as part of Algeria's squad for the [[2011 CAF U-23 Championship]] in [[Morocco]].<ref>[http://www.dzfoot.com/news-10307/en-u23-les-21-joueurs-selectionnes/ EN U23 : Les 21 joueurs sélectionnés]; DZFoot, November 16, 2011.</ref>
