'''Nevvare Hanım''' (4 May 1901 – 22 June 1992) was the fourth wife of Sultan [[Mehmed VI]] of the [[Ottoman Empire]].{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=263}}

==Early life==
Nevvare Hanım was born on 4 May 1901{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=263}} in Derbent, [[Ottoman Empire]].{{sfn|Açba|2004|p=194}} Born as Ayşe Çıhçı, she was a member of [[Abkhazians|Abkhazian]] noble family, Çıhçı. Her father was Mustafa Bey Çıhcı, the son of Süleyman Bey Çıhçı. Her mother was Hafize Hanım Kap-Ipha, the daughter of Nevruz Bey Kap-Ipha.{{sfn|Açba|2004|p=77}}{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=196}} She had two elder siblings, Şefika Hanım and Ahmet Şükrü Bey, and four younger siblings, Hasan Bey, Fikri Bey, Halime Hanım and Hacer Nüvit Hanım.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=199}} Through her grandfather, she was related to [[Müveddet Kadın]], third wife of Sultan [[Mehmed VI]], whose grandfather Mat Bey was a brother of Süleyman Bey.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=194, 196}} 

As a young child, she had been sent to live-in Mehmed's Çengelköy mansion when he had been a prince, where after sometime she became a lady-in-waiting to Müveddet Kadın. Her name according to the costum of the Ottoman court was Nevvare.{{sfn|Açba|2004|p=75}}{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=196}}

==First marriage==
Nevvare married Mehmed on 20 June 1918 in the [[Dolmabahçe Palace]].{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=263}}{{sfn|Sakaoğlu|2008|p=707}}{{sfn|Açba|2004|p=194}} Mehmed was fifty seven, while Nevvare was seventeen years old. Nevvare remained childless.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=197}} After Mehmed's accession to the throne on 4 July 1918,<ref>{{cite book|first=Sylvia|last=Kedourie|title=Turkey: Identity, Democracy, Politics|publisher=Routledge|year=February 4, 2014|pages=22|isbn=978-1-135-22946-7}}</ref> She was given the title of "Baş Ikbal".{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=197}} 

After Mehmed's deposition in 1922, he was sent into exile in [[Sanremo|San Remo]]. She, like rest of the family members, was imprisoned in [[Feriye Palace]]. Although, she wanted to go to San Remo, however, because of her illness, she went to live-in with her family in Derbent. The two divorced on 20 May 1924 on her request.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=197}}{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=263}}

==Second marriage==
Nevvare returned to Istanbul, and married a trader named Mevlüd  Sönmezler in 1926, and took the name Leyla Sönmezler. They first settled in Ferenyolu, then in [[Şişli]]. In the beginning of 1970s they settled in Derbent.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=197-8}} Her husband died in 1974.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=199}}

==Death==
Nevvare died on 22 June 1992 in her mansion in Derbent, and was buried in a cemetery in Derbent.{{sfn|Açba|2004|p=194}}{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=198}}

