'''Richard Hemming MW''' is a London-based wine writer, educator, and a [[Master of Wine]].<ref name=IMWRH>{{cite web|last=The Institute of Masters of Wine|url=http://www.mastersofwine.org/en/meet-the-masters/profile/index.cfm/id/f7b8a043-5e4b-e211-a20600155d6d822c|website=mastersofwine.org|title=Richard Hemming MW Profile|accessdate=2015-08-10}}</ref>

==Biography==
British wine writer Richard Hemming has worked in wine since 2001. His early roles within the wine industry include being a viticultural assistant at Gusbourne Estate in Kent and six years in UK retail management with Majestic Wine.<ref name=SSRH>{{cite web|url=http://www.sipandsavour.co.uk/speakers-2/richard-hemming|website=sipandsavour.co.uk|title=Richard Hemming on Sip & Savour|accessdate=2015-08-10}}</ref><ref name=WFW>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldoffinewine.com/WineListAwardsSearch/WineAwardsJudgesDetails/11|website=worldoffinewine.com|title=The World of Fine Wine Awards Judge Details|accessdate=2015-08-10}}</ref>

Hemming started working with [[Jancis Robinson|Jancis Robinson MW]] in 2008 and has since been writing regularly for the website JancisRobinson.com ever since.<ref name=JR>{{cite web|last=Robinson|first=Jancis|url=http://www.jancisrobinson.com/articles/richard-hemming-mw|website=jancisrobinson.com|title=Richard Hemming MW|accessdate=2015-08-10}}</ref> He has also been published by the [[Financial Times]], [[Decanter (magazine)|Decanter]], [[The_Drinks_Business_(magazine)|The Drinks Business]], Harpers Wine & Spirit, [[The World of Fine Wine]], Noble Rot and has a monthly wine column in the Off Licence News. Notable distinctions includes being shortlisted as the Louis Roederer International Feature Writer Of The Year 2015.<ref name=LRA>{{cite web|url=http://www.theroedererawards.com/categories/feature-writer/|website=theroedererawards.com|title=Louis Roederer International Wine Writers' Awards Feature Writer|accessdate=2015-08-10}}</ref>

Alongside writing, Richard also judges in competitions such as the [[Decanter World Wine Awards]] and teaches wine courses for companies and private clients.<ref name=DWWA>{{cite web|url=http://www.decanter.com/interviews/meet-the-dwwa-2013-judges-richard-hemming-22068/|website=decanter.com|title=Meet the Judges: Richard Hemming|accessdate=2015-08-10}}</ref>

In September 2015, Richard Hemming became one of only 340 Masters of Wine in the world.<ref name=IMWPR>{{cite web|last=The Institute of Masters of Wine|url=http://www.mastersofwine.org/en/news/index.cfm/id/AE2D74B9-76C9-4A47-B6519F5560514F0A|website=mastersofwine.org|title=PRESS RELEASE: A record number of 19 new Masters of Wine announced|accessdate=2015-07-10}}</ref> After passing the theory exam in 2011 and tasting in 2012, his final research paper to complete the highest qualification at the [[Master of Wine|Institute of Masters of Wine]] focused on ''How have trends in the publication of consumer wine books changed since 1914, and how does this inform their present prospects?''

